  "texts": [
    "According to the authors, the bias in PER may cause its low performance in continuous learning algorithms that depend on the MSE.",
    "In addition, they demonstrated that the importance sampling ratios used by PER can be absorbed in the loss function itself, simplifying the algorithm.",
    "PER uses importance sampling in weighting the loss function to reduce the bias introduced by prioritization.",
    "However, it is no longer biased when using the MSE and setting the hyperparameter β = 1 (see Sect. 4).",
    "As the expected gradient can absorb the prioritization, PER can be unbiased even without using importance sampling if the expected gradient is still meaningful."
  ],
